TY  - JOUR
T1  - Domestic Trade Frictions and Agriculture
AU  - Sotelo, Sebastian
Y1  - 2019/10/14
PY  - 2019
DA  - 2020/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/706859
DO  - 10.1086/706859
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 2690
EP  - 2738
VL  - 128
IS  - 7
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - I develop a model of agriculture on heterogeneous land to study the relation between trade, productivity, and welfare in Peru, where farmers face high internal and external trade costs. I quantify the model with new data on crop prices, yields, and land allocations. I then measure the effects of changes to trade opportunities. A policy of paving roads raises aggregate productivity (4.9%) and the median farmer?s welfare (2.7%), but increased competition from remote suppliers harms 20% of farmers. An increase in international grain prices spreads unevenly across regions, benefiting farmers but hurting urban consumers close to ports.
AB  - I develop a model of agriculture on heterogeneous land to study the relation between trade, productivity, and welfare in Peru, where farmers face high internal and external trade costs. I quantify the model with new data on crop prices, yields, and land allocations. I then measure the effects of changes to trade opportunities. A policy of paving roads raises aggregate productivity (4.9%) and the median farmer?s welfare (2.7%), but increased competition from remote suppliers harms 20% of farmers. An increase in international grain prices spreads unevenly across regions, benefiting farmers but hurting urban consumers close to ports.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/706859
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/706859
Y2  - 2024/03/20
